{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d0bb2bb-a804-49b0-ac03-97f424e92ba5","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the diagnostic/reporting options move behind `--` and use new switch names:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura\n```\n\n**Required package references** (add to your test project):\n\n| Old behaviour | New package |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n\n`--filter` stays on the `dotnet test` side (before `--`) because the platform honours the same filter expressions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"de90dd1e-eced-4401-b59d-dd6c08c710b2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage or you use a different mechanism\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nI need to clarify how arguments map when using `dotnet test` with the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform, since the command structure changes slightly compared to the traditional VSTest runner.\n\nThe key mappings are: `--filter` stays mostly the same, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, code coverage collection shifts to `--collect-coverage` with format options, crash dumps use `--crashdump`, and hang detection uses `--hangdump` with timeout settings. Each of these newer options requires specific NuGet packages to be installed. When invoking through `dotnet test`, these arguments get passed directly to the test executable.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8, the test project runs as a standalone executable, so you can either invoke it directly with the platform-specific flags or run it through `dotnet test` as a wrapper, passing the arguments after `--`. I need to note which NuGet packages are required for each of those command-line options to work properly with the Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":1295,"requestId":"286B:1A3A99:15679F8:16D2505:6A046010"},"id":"40f4231d-b6b9-4bfd-ae5e-c81f6544fb32","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:27:39.660Z","parentId":"58902d21-7f17-4a73-bb14-be0e2969efc7"}
